{
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "$schema": "https://docs.oasis-open.org/sarif/sarif/v2.1.0/errata01/os/schemas/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "grype",
          "version": "0.114.0",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/anchore/grype",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-45447-libssl3t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-45447 high vulnerability for libssl3t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: A specially crafted PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed message could trigger a use-after-free during PKCS#7 signature verification.  Impact summary: A use-after-free may result in process crashes, heap corruption, or potentially remote code execution.  When processing a PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed message, if the SignedData digestAlgorithms field is present as an empty ASN.1 SET, OpenSSL may incorrectly free a caller-owned BIO during PKCS7_verify(). A subsequent use of the BIO by the calling application results in a use-after-free condition.  In the common case this occurs when the application later calls BIO_free() on the BIO originally passed to PKCS7_verify(). Depending on allocator behavior and application-specific BIO usage patterns, this may result in a crash or other memory corruption. In some application contexts this may potentially be exploitable for remote code execution.  Applications that process PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed messages using OpenSSL PKCS#7 APIs may be affected. Applications using the CMS APIs for this processing are not affected.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue, as the affected code is outside the OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447\nSeverity: high\nPackage: libssl3t64\nVersion: 3.6.2-1\nFix Version: 3.6.3-1\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-45447](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | libssl3t64  | 3.6.2-1  | 3.6.3-1  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-45447](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssl3t64@3.6.2-1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openssl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "8.8"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-45447-openssl-provider-legacy",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-45447 high vulnerability for openssl-provider-legacy package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: A specially crafted PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed message could trigger a use-after-free during PKCS#7 signature verification.  Impact summary: A use-after-free may result in process crashes, heap corruption, or potentially remote code execution.  When processing a PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed message, if the SignedData digestAlgorithms field is present as an empty ASN.1 SET, OpenSSL may incorrectly free a caller-owned BIO during PKCS7_verify(). A subsequent use of the BIO by the calling application results in a use-after-free condition.  In the common case this occurs when the application later calls BIO_free() on the BIO originally passed to PKCS7_verify(). Depending on allocator behavior and application-specific BIO usage patterns, this may result in a crash or other memory corruption. In some application contexts this may potentially be exploitable for remote code execution.  Applications that process PKCS#7 or S/MIME signed messages using OpenSSL PKCS#7 APIs may be affected. Applications using the CMS APIs for this processing are not affected.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue, as the affected code is outside the OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447\nSeverity: high\nPackage: openssl-provider-legacy\nVersion: 3.6.2-1\nFix Version: 3.6.3-1\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-45447](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-45447**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | openssl-provider-legacy  | 3.6.2-1  | 3.6.3-1  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-45447](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-45447)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/openssl-provider-legacy@3.6.2-1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openssl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "8.8"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42764-libssl3t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42764 high vulnerability for libssl3t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: Receiving a QUIC initial packet with an invalid token may trigger a NULL pointer dereference in the OpenSSL QUIC server with address validation disabled.  Impact summary: NULL pointer dereference typically causes abnormal termination of the affected QUIC server process and a Denial of Service.  If the address validation is disabled in the OpenSSL QUIC server implementation, an attacker can crash the server by sending an initial packet with an invalid or expired token.  By default, the client address validation is enabled in the OpenSSL QUIC server implementation, which makes the default configuration not vulnerable to this issue. However if the SSL_LISTENER_FLAG_NO_VALIDATE is used with the SSL_new_listener() call, the address validation is disabled making the vulnerable code reachable.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue, as the affected code is outside the OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42764\nSeverity: high\nPackage: libssl3t64\nVersion: 3.6.2-1\nFix Version: 3.6.3-1\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42764](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42764**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | libssl3t64  | 3.6.2-1  | 3.6.3-1  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42764](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssl3t64@3.6.2-1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openssl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42764-openssl-provider-legacy",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42764 high vulnerability for openssl-provider-legacy package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: Receiving a QUIC initial packet with an invalid token may trigger a NULL pointer dereference in the OpenSSL QUIC server with address validation disabled.  Impact summary: NULL pointer dereference typically causes abnormal termination of the affected QUIC server process and a Denial of Service.  If the address validation is disabled in the OpenSSL QUIC server implementation, an attacker can crash the server by sending an initial packet with an invalid or expired token.  By default, the client address validation is enabled in the OpenSSL QUIC server implementation, which makes the default configuration not vulnerable to this issue. However if the SSL_LISTENER_FLAG_NO_VALIDATE is used with the SSL_new_listener() call, the address validation is disabled making the vulnerable code reachable.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue, as the affected code is outside the OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42764\nSeverity: high\nPackage: openssl-provider-legacy\nVersion: 3.6.2-1\nFix Version: 3.6.3-1\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42764](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42764**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | openssl-provider-legacy  | 3.6.2-1  | 3.6.3-1  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42764](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42764)  |\n"
