              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-34183-libssl3t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-34183 high vulnerability for libssl3t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: Remote peer may exhaust heap memory of the QUIC server or client by flooding it with packets containing PATH_CHALLENGE frames.  Impact summary: A malicious remote peer can cause an unbounded memory allocation which can lead to an abnormal termination of the application acting as a QUIC client or server and a Denial of Service.  A remote peer may exhaust heap memory by flooding the local QUIC stack with PATH_CHALLENGE frames. The local QUIC stack allocates a PATH_RESPONSE frame for every PATH_CHALLENGE it receives. The allocated PATH_RESPONSE frame gets freed only when the remote peer acknowledges reception of the PATH_RESPONSE frame which will not be done by a malicious peer.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue. The QUIC stack is outside of OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-34183",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-34183\nSeverity: high\nPackage: libssl3t64\nVersion: 3.6.2-1\nFix Version: 3.6.3-1\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-34183](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-34183)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-34183**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | libssl3t64  | 3.6.2-1  | 3.6.3-1  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-34183](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-34183)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libssl3t64@3.6.2-1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openssl"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-34183-openssl-provider-legacy",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-34183 high vulnerability for openssl-provider-legacy package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Issue summary: Remote peer may exhaust heap memory of the QUIC server or client by flooding it with packets containing PATH_CHALLENGE frames.  Impact summary: A malicious remote peer can cause an unbounded memory allocation which can lead to an abnormal termination of the application acting as a QUIC client or server and a Denial of Service.  A remote peer may exhaust heap memory by flooding the local QUIC stack with PATH_CHALLENGE frames. The local QUIC stack allocates a PATH_RESPONSE frame for every PATH_CHALLENGE it receives. The allocated PATH_RESPONSE frame gets freed only when the remote peer acknowledges reception of the PATH_RESPONSE frame which will not be done by a malicious peer.  The FIPS modules in 4.0, 3.6, 3.5, 3.4, and 3.0 are not affected by this issue. The QUIC stack is outside of OpenSSL FIPS module boundary."
              },
