            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42497-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42497 high vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Archive::Tar versions before 3.08 for Perl extract hardlinks to attacker controlled paths outside the extraction directory.  _make_special_file() passes the tar header's linkname to link() without validating it against absolute paths or .. segments, creating a hardlink that shares the victim file's inode.  A subsequent write through the extracted name modifies the victim file, and the post-extraction chmod, chown, and utime block in _extract_file() (guarded only against symlinks via -l) applies the tar header's mode, owner, and timestamps to the shared inode during extraction alone."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42497\nSeverity: high\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-7+b1\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42497](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42497**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-7+b1  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42497](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42497)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-7%2Bb1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl%405.40.1-7"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-48959-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-48959 high vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "IO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.220 for Perl allow CPU exhaustion via per-byte read loop in fastForward.  fastForward() compares length $offset (the digit count of the offset, 1 to 19) against the chunk size $c instead of $offset itself, so $c shrinks from 16 KiB to 1-19 bytes per iteration.  Extracting a named entry from an attacker supplied zip via IO::Uncompress::Unzip-\u003enew($zip, Name =\u003e $target) drives a per-byte read loop scaling with the entry's compressed size, up to the non-Zip64 4 GiB cap."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48959",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-48959\nSeverity: high\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-7+b1\nFix Version: 5.40.1-8\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-48959](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48959)",
